<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CodeLingo - Privacy & Data Protection Policy</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; line-height: 1.7; color: #2d3436; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 20px; background-color: #f8fafc; }
        .container { background: #ffffff; padding: 50px; border-radius: 20px; box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; }
        .header-box { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px; border-bottom: 2px solid #edf2f7; padding-bottom: 30px; }
        h1 { color: #10b981; font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; }
        .brand { color: #059669; font-weight: 600; }
        h2 { color: #1e293b; margin-top: 35px; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; display: flex; align-items: center; }
        h2::before { content: ""; display: inline-block; width: 4px; height: 20px; background: #10b981; margin-right: 12px; border-radius: 2px; }
        p, li { font-size: 15px; color: #475569; }
        ul { padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: square; }
        .highlight-box { background: #f0fdf4; border-left: 4px solid #10b981; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; }
        .footer { margin-top: 60px; font-size: 13px; color: #94a3b8; text-align: center; border-top: 1px solid #f1f5f9; padding-top: 30px; }
        .badge { display: inline-block; padding: 4px 12px; background: #ecfdf5; color: #065f46; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 20px; }
        .action-link { color: #10b981; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header-box">
            <div class="badge">SECURE LEARNING ENVIRONMENT</div>
            <h1>Privacy & Data Protection Policy</h1>
            <p><strong>CodeLingo Official Documentation</strong></p>
            <p>Effective Date: April 6, 2026 | Version 1.2</p>
        </div>

        <p>At <span class="brand">CodeLingo</span>, we believe that learning to code should not come at the cost of your privacy. We are committed to protecting the personal data of our users through <strong>transparent data practices</strong> and <strong>industry-standard security protocols</strong>.</p>

        <div class="highlight-box">
            <strong>Core Principle:</strong> We only collect data that is strictly necessary to provide a gamified learning experience. We never sell your data to third-party brokers.
        </div>

        <h2>1. Data Collection & Source</h2>
        <p>We process information provided directly by you and generated through your interaction with the App:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Authentication Data:</strong> When you use Google Sign-In, we receive your unique User ID, email, and profile name. This is handled securely via <strong>Firebase Authentication</strong>.</li>
            <li><strong>Educational Progress:</strong> To provide a continuous experience, we store your XP (Experience Points), completed modules, daily streaks, and "Heart" balances.</li>
            <li><strong>Technical Identifiers:</strong> We collect anonymized device IDs and crash reports to maintain app stability and optimize performance.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Service Delivery:</strong> Managing your account and synchronizing progress across devices.</li>
            <li><strong>Gamification:</strong> Calculating leaderboard positions and streak rewards.</li>
            <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Sending critical system updates or "Daily Reminder" notifications.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Third-Party Integrations & Security</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Google Firebase:</strong> Secure cloud infrastructure for data storage.</li>
            <li><strong>AdMob by Google:</strong> Used for serving rewarded ads. We do not share your learning history with advertisers.</li>
            <li><strong>RevenueCat:</strong> Secure bridge for managing in-app transactions without storing credit card details.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Data Retention & Account Deletion</h2>
        <p>We retain your information as long as your account is active. Users have the <strong>Right to be Forgotten</strong> and can exercise their data deletion rights at any time.</p>
        <div class="highlight-box" style="background: #fff7ed; border-color: #f97316;">
            <strong>How to Delete Your Account:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>In-App:</strong> Go to Settings > Account > Delete Account. This will immediately trigger the deletion of your Firebase profile and progress data.</li>
                <li><strong>Web Request:</strong> If you cannot access the app, you can request full account and data deletion by emailing us at <a href="mailto:zediswow@gmail.com" class="action-link">zediswow@gmail.com</a>. Please use the subject line "Account Deletion Request".</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>5. Global Compliance (GDPR, KVKK, CCPA)</h2>
        <p>Regardless of your location, we provide high standards of privacy rights, including the right to access your data, the right to rectification, and the right to data portability.</p>

        <h2>6. Security Measures</h2>
        <p>We implement <strong>End-to-End Encryption (E2EE)</strong> for data transfers and utilize Firebase’s robust security rules to ensure that only you can access your personal data.</p>

        <h2>7. Contact Our Privacy Team</h2>
        <p>For any privacy-related inquiries or data requests, please reach out:</p>
        <p style="font-weight: 600; color: #10b981;">Email: zediswow@gmail.com</p>

        <div class="footer">
            &copy; 2026 CodeLingo. This document is subject to updates to comply with evolving international laws. <br>
            <strong>"Coding the future, protecting your presence."</strong>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
